ops.insert: His lessons on kindness continue to shape my actions and relationships every day. One of the things he has done which has made a big difference in my life is showing that we must respect everyone, and treat everyone with kindness, even when a person is mean/rude to you. It is not possible to know what the person is going through behind closed doors. The only thing that matters is whether or not you try to be a good person, and make the best of every situation that you are in. He taught me that you must always try to be your best self, and try to be a bright light. He also taught me that the way that we treat people of "less" than us shows a lot about our character. For example, one should always be nice to people  at the grocery store. It is not possible to know what they went through to end up in this situation. We must not try to make their life harder, and must be a positive experience. His example inspires me to spread kindness, hoping to brighten someone else's day just like he did for me. $Discuss a experience$ One time, I helped a stranger pick up their groceries. This stranger was an old man, and I saw him struggling to pick everything up. I asked him whether he needed assistance, and he said yes.
